AKURE – Africa Democratic Congress (ADC), Akure South Local Government chapter, in Ondo State, has collapsed its structures and joined All Progressives Congress (APC) in the state ahead of the 2020 governorship election. This was contained in a statement signed by the APC Director, Media & Publicity, Steve Otaloro, and made available to Daily Independent on Sunday. The leader of the ADC defectors,. Femi Bello, gave the reason for the defection as a decision by members of the party to identity with the performance and track record of the Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu-led administration within the short time in office. He emphasised on the rapid development that has taken place in Akure, adding that the governor has been good to Akure as a city and as the state capital. The state chairman of APC, Ade Adetimehin, who welcomed the defectors to his party, said that Akure could comfortably be referred to as a befitting modern state capital with functional 21st century infrastructure made possible by the APC-led government in the state. He said Akeredolu has turned the state into a big construction site of different developmental projects across all the senatorial districts of the state. Adetimehin expressed delight in the decision of the ADC members, saying it was an incident of joy to receive members of the ADC who decided to join the APC out of their own volition. Speaking further on the achievements of the governor, the APC chairman said: “The governor went straight to work in spite of the huge debt he met on assumption of office. “